                "name": "Mark Kisenwether",
                "href": "/profile/Mark-Kisenwether"
            },
            "answer_text": "Can a bar of soap get dirty, or is it self-cleaning because it's soap? It depends if you're asking about real soap made with fats and sodium hydroxide or fake soap made with anything other than fats and sodium hydroxide. Real soap does not typically harbor bacteria or other crud provided it's rinsed off well. Now, if you goober it all up and don't rinse it, sure the crud is going to stay on it. On the other hand, fake soap, are especially those containing things like moisturizer and fragrance, will tends to harbor more crud even when rinsed because the crud sticks to the residuals that stick to your skin and the fake soap itself. If you're really concerned about getting clean, use real soap or a non-residual detergent like Ajax dish detergent. When I don't have time to make my own soap, I use Zote brand. - MarkKw ",
