                "name": "Palash Dhir",
                "href": "/profile/Palash-Dhir"
            },
            "answer_text": "Yes, a bar of soap does indeed get dirty. That's how it gets your hands clean: by latching onto grease, dirt and oil more strongly than your skin does. Of course, when you're using soap, you're washing all those loose, dirt-trapping, dirty soap molecules away, but a bar of soap can also be contaminated with microorganisms.Dirty soap can't clean itself, though. A contaminated bar of soap gets cleaned by the same mechanical action that helps clean you up when you wash your hands: Scrubbing. ",
